The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of visual concept detection in images from the Multilingual Visual Sentiment Ontology (MVSO) using deep learning techniques. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also discusses parameter tuning and training runs, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper mentions tag-restricted queries for higher fidelity labels, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
